drug.name: Labetuzumab
drug.description: Labetuzumab is a humanized monoclonal antibody to carcinoembryonic antigen that inhibits tumor growth. It is used in radioimmunotherapy.

article.citation: Liersch T, Meller J, Kulle B, Behr TM, Markus P, Langer C, Ghadimi BM, Wegener WA, Kovacs J, Horak ID, Becker H, Goldenberg DM: Phase II trial of carcinoembryonic antigen radioimmunotherapy with 131I-labetuzumab after salvage resection of colorectal metastases in the liver: five-year safety and efficacy results. J Clin Oncol. 2005 Sep 20;23(27):6763-70.

Liersch T, Meller J, Bittrich M, Kulle B, Becker H, Goldenberg DM: Update of carcinoembryonic antigen radioimmunotherapy with (131)I-labetuzumab after salvage resection of colorectal liver metastases: comparison of outcome to a contemporaneous control group. Ann Surg Oncol. 2007 Sep;14(9):2577-90. Epub 2007 Jun 15.

drug.indication: Labetuzumab is a humanized monoclonal antibody used to treat cancer. Retrieved from "http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Labetuzumab"
drug.mechanism-of-action: labetuzumab could significantly increase the chemosensitivity of human colon and breast cancer cells in vitro to several anticancer drugs.
